HEADWORD: Swordbill
<hw>Sword"bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A humming bird (<spn>Docimastes ensiferus</spn>) having a very
long, slender bill, exceeding the length of the body of the
bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sworded</ent>⟦br⟧
